    // print the value of the integer
	printf("Value: %d\n", *p);
    // free the memory
	free(p);
    return 0;
}
```

Output:

```
Value: 5
```

In this example, we allocated memory for an integer using malloc(), set its value to 5, printed the value of the integer, and then freed the memory using free().

