## Memory Leaks

Memory leaks are a common problem in C programming. A memory leak occurs when a program allocates memory on the heap but fails to free the memory when it is no longer needed. This results in a program using more memory than it needs, and eventually running out of memory.

Memory leaks can be difficult to track down, especially if the program is large and complex. It can be difficult to determine where the memory is being allocated and freed, and it can be difficult to determine exactly when the memory is no longer needed.

