## Memory Leaks

A memory leak is a programming error that causes a program to use more memory than it needs. Memory leaks can cause a program to use more memory than it needs, which can cause the program to slow down or crash.

A memory leak occurs when a program allocates memory on the heap but does not free the memory when it is no longer needed. This can cause a program to use more memory than it needs, which can cause the program to slow down or crash.

