## String Concatenation

The `strcat` function concatenates two strings. The following program demonstrates how to use the `strcat` function to concatenate two strings:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    const char* message1 = "Hello";
    const char* message2 = "World";
